            menu:
                '“‘Tis hard to say, aye? What do travelers need?” He clears his throat and turns away to have a look at his store. While some of the crates and barrels are empty, they carry an assortment of odds and ends. Tools made of wood and stone, pots, mugs, seeds, vegetables, fabric. It takes him a few minutes to look through the wares.
                \n\nHe puts three packages on the countertop, and as he unwraps the first one, you recognize what it is by the shape alone.
                \n\n“Tell me this is ne a beauty!” He chuckles and lets you hold the shiny battle axe. The haft is long, but the head is light. “I know what you’re thinking. Your eyes say everything!” He praises the weapon loudly, but you barely listen to him. You see your reflection in the unused blade, as sharp as they get. You’re not a smith, but you see not a spot of rust. When you take a swing, it takes hardly any effort. The leather straps holding the pieces together are just a decoration, and the handle is as smooth as glass and perfectly fits into your hand...
